# Model served by vLLM. SigLIP2 is natively covered by vLLM's SiglipModel
# (text+image dual encoder), so no `--model-impl transformers` is needed.
# Fallback (only if siglip2 genuinely fails to load): google/siglip-base-patch16-224
VLLM_MODEL=google/siglip2-base-patch16-224
# SigLIP wants image-only requests to carry an EMPTY text prompt. The default
# chat template renders text tokens, which vLLM's SigLIP rejects ("not both").
# This custom template emits only text parts (empty for an image-only message),
# so the image arrives as mm_data with an empty prompt.
VLLM_EXTRA_ARGS=--chat-template /work/siglip_image_template.jinja
OMP_NUM_THREADS=16
